snippet.title: Central Georgia's top news stories for December 2, 2021
snippet.description:
Stacey Abrams has announced she will launch another campaign to become the nation's first Black woman governor. The Northeast High's basketball coach and athletic director was selected for the position in November. The Salvation Army made Christmas possible for Melissa White and her siblings when they were children, so now she's making sure today's kids have a good Christmas.
